


npx tsc --init --rootdir src --outdir lib

npx tsc --watch


1° npx tsc --init --rootdir src --outdir lib:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This command initializes a new TypeScript project.
The tsc --init command creates a tsconfig.json file in your project directory.
This file specifies the root files and the compiler options required to compile the project.
The --rootdir src option specifies that the root files of your TypeScript project are in the 'src' directory.
The --outdir lib option specifies that the output (compiled JavaScript files) should be placed in the 'lib' directory.

2° npx tsc --watch:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This command then starts the TypeScript compiler in watch mode.
The compiler will automatically recompile your project whenever any of your TypeScript files are changed.
This is handy during development as it means you do not need to manually recompile your code after making changes.



